1
00:01:29,539 --> 00:01:34,940
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,350 --> 00:01:37,789
[Episode 18]

3
00:01:38,009 --> 00:01:41,720
[Aoxun Technology]

4
00:01:38,509 --> 00:01:39,000
Ms. Zhao,

5
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,009
you're not off work yet?

6
00:01:40,009 --> 00:01:40,810
Well, Xia Lei,

7
00:01:41,070 --> 00:01:41,950
I've got an emergency here.

8
00:01:41,950 --> 00:01:42,860
Please do me a favor.

9
00:01:42,860 --> 00:01:44,259
What's wrong? What is it?

10
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:45,940
I've seen your resume.

11
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,039
You majored in
Communication Engineering, right?

12
00:01:48,039 --> 00:01:50,039
So you must understand networking.

13
00:01:50,160 --> 00:01:51,070
A little, I'd say.

14
00:01:51,070 --> 00:01:53,560
I used to run a networking company
with a friend.

15
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:54,479
That's great.

16
00:01:55,150 --> 00:01:56,590
Our company's server room network

17
00:01:56,590 --> 00:01:57,789
suddenly ran into a problem today,

18
00:01:57,789 --> 00:01:58,759
but the repair technician said

19
00:01:58,759 --> 00:02:00,710
he still has several jobs ahead of ours.

20
00:02:00,710 --> 00:02:02,230
He probably won't be able to
get to it today.

21
00:02:02,230 --> 00:02:04,740
I can't stay here waiting until midnight,
you know.

22
00:02:04,740 --> 00:02:06,100
Xia Lei, how about

23
00:02:06,350 --> 00:02:07,950
you go take a look at it for me?

24
00:02:08,030 --> 00:02:09,190
Okay, I can try.

25
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:10,830
Great.

26
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:14,160
I'll leave it to you then,

27
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:15,200
networking genius.

28
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:16,190
I'm counting on you.

29
00:02:16,190 --> 00:02:16,800
Okay.

30
00:02:17,750 --> 00:02:18,590
I'm leaving then.

31
00:02:18,590 --> 00:02:18,960
Bye-bye.

32
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:19,490
Bye-bye.

33
00:02:24,030 --> 00:02:24,680
Xia Lei.

34
00:02:25,470 --> 00:02:27,670
You just take on everything, don't you?

35
00:02:28,340 --> 00:02:31,340
Isn't this basically the same as
what we did at school?

36
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:37,750
Push harder.

37
00:02:40,390 --> 00:02:41,280
Come on.

38
00:02:57,430 --> 00:02:58,530
Surprised, huh?

39
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,150
Totally surprised!

40
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:01,240
Unexpected, huh?

41
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:02,440
Totally unexpected!

42
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:03,910
Look at you.

43
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,520
You're about to become a big boss
in no time.

44
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:06,190
Good for you.

45
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:07,000
You bet.

46
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,260
Look, such a huge caravan.

47
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:12,080
Business is going to get really big.

48
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:14,430
Going from a tricycle to this
is just a transition.

49
00:03:14,430 --> 00:03:16,370
Later, it'll grow into a full store—

50
00:03:16,370 --> 00:03:20,030
the biggest fashion store
in the entire East Chemical Plant area.

51
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:21,680
This outfit is really pretty.

52
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:22,400
Where did you get it?

53
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:24,360
This? I bought it at the big caravan

54
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:26,680
right by the entrance. JM Jeans.

55
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:27,500
-Is it cheap?
-It is.

56
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:28,310
You know what?

57
00:03:28,310 --> 00:03:29,800
If you mention my name Chunchun,

58
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:31,030
they'll give you a discount.

59
00:03:31,030 --> 00:03:31,960
It fits perfectly. You look great in it.

60
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:33,220
How much is this, boss?

61
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,360
240.

62
00:03:34,710 --> 00:03:35,800
240? That's way too expensive.

63
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,430
Xiaoman.

64
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:38,430
The clothes are selling really fast.

65
00:03:38,430 --> 00:03:39,280
Time to restock.

66
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,030
Where have you been?

67
00:03:40,030 --> 00:03:40,710
Help out, okay?

68
00:03:40,710 --> 00:03:42,570
I can't handle this all by myself.

69
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:44,430
Can you give me a better price?

70
00:03:44,430 --> 00:03:45,400
I already bought a scarf.

71
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,360
What price do you have in mind?

72
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:46,840
Here, Miss.

73
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:49,040
-I've packed it for you.
-How about 200?

74
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:51,400
This is the 36th piece I've modeled
for your sake.

75
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,660
You're keeping count?

76
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:54,180
I went in there to see you just now.

77
00:03:54,180 --> 00:03:55,360
That outfit looks amazing on you.

78
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,180
Look at yourself.

79
00:03:56,180 --> 00:03:57,640
You look like a superstar.

80
00:03:57,660 --> 00:03:59,750
I told you I have an eye for these things.

81
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:01,280
Remember our deal?

82
00:04:01,470 --> 00:04:04,030
I get a 10% commission
on each piece of clothing.

83
00:04:04,030 --> 00:04:05,700
It's been 10 days. Pay up.

84
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:07,520
I never said that.

85
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:10,190
It's 10% of the profit.

86
00:04:10,310 --> 00:04:11,470
Who are you trying to scam here?

87
00:04:11,470 --> 00:04:12,960
Don't you know

88
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:14,240
how much profit these crappy clothes make?

89
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:15,120
Trying to fool me?

90
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:15,910
Chunchun,

91
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:16,920
you saw it for yourself.

92
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,630
People at our factory
are too good at haggling.

93
00:04:18,630 --> 00:04:20,329
We haven't even recovered our costs yet.

94
00:04:20,329 --> 00:04:21,459
I don't care. Pay up.

95
00:04:22,470 --> 00:04:24,440
Xiaoman's the one who promised you, right?

96
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:26,560
Go ask whoever made the promise
for the money.

97
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:27,160
Xiaoman!

98
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,610
Boss Zhang, come on.

99
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:29,040
What is it?

100
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,630
Chunchun wants to talk to you.

101
00:04:30,630 --> 00:04:31,950
What is it? You aren't doing any work,

102
00:04:31,950 --> 00:04:32,980
just sitting here chatting.

103
00:04:32,980 --> 00:04:34,040
Well, I don't know.

104
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:35,120
What's up?

105
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:35,920
Pay me my wages.

106
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,800
You promised me 10% of the profit
from each piece.

107
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,200
It's been 10 days. Pay up.

108
00:04:39,270 --> 00:04:40,159
Yeah, pay her.

109
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:41,270
Pay for what?

110
00:04:41,390 --> 00:04:42,040
Commission.

111
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:42,680
You promised her.

112
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:43,510
Why should I pay?

113
00:04:43,510 --> 00:04:44,560
Is this just my business?

114
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:45,180
Aren't you part of it too?

115
00:04:45,180 --> 00:04:46,260
Isn't the money with you?

116
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:48,000
That money you gave me was for gas.

117
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:48,720
What do you mean for gas?

118
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,720
Isn't the bulk of the money with you?

119
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:50,750
How is the bulk of it with me?

120
00:04:50,750 --> 00:04:52,480
I only have the gas money.
You have the bulk of it.

121
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:53,720
I always give you 100

122
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:54,630
and keep 50 for myself.

123
00:04:54,630 --> 00:04:55,480
Hurry up. You promised her.

124
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:56,240
Just pay her.

125
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:57,310
No can do.

126
00:04:57,330 --> 00:04:58,300
What do you mean no can do?

127
00:04:58,300 --> 00:04:58,890
What's that supposed to mean?

128
00:04:58,890 --> 00:05:00,820
Enough. I'll give you two options.

129
00:05:00,830 --> 00:05:03,240
One, pay me
the 10% commission immediately;

130
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:05,000
or two, 30 yuan a day.

131
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,000
Pick one.

132
00:05:06,050 --> 00:05:06,610
Pick one.

133
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:08,480
The first one is better.

134
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,160
Why the first one?

135
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,020
Are you stupid?

136
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:12,360
The second's 30 a day, and you think
the first one is better?

137
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:13,720
According to my calculation,
the first one is indeed better.

138
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:15,690
Don't you know how many pieces
we sell a day?

139
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:16,800
I don't care. You pay.

140
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,410
Don't worry. I'll give it to you.

141
00:05:17,410 --> 00:05:18,750
I'll take it out of today's sales.

142
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:19,510
This...

143
00:05:20,070 --> 00:05:21,530
Why sweat over this money?

144
00:05:23,630 --> 00:05:24,430
For 4 days.

145
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:25,900
Five days.

146
00:05:26,510 --> 00:05:27,950
This is for a week.

147
00:05:29,070 --> 00:05:30,630
I'll hold onto the other 3 days' pay
for now

148
00:05:30,630 --> 00:05:31,390
and give it to you later.

149
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:32,990
What do you mean hold onto it?

150
00:05:33,350 --> 00:05:34,120
What?

151
00:05:34,150 --> 00:05:35,480
That's already a lot, okay?

152
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:37,490
-I'm leaving.
-You're unbelievable.

153
00:05:37,490 --> 00:05:39,090
Help model our clothes more.

154
00:05:39,390 --> 00:05:41,830
Who allowed you to act on your own!

155
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:44,750
Look what you did!

156
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,950
Now nobody can work!

157
00:05:48,430 --> 00:05:49,290
What happened?

158
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,750
Xia Lei tried to fix the network
in the server room last night,

159
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:55,159
and he ended up blowing up
the entire network

160
00:05:55,159 --> 00:05:56,020
of our company.

161
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,760
Explain yourselves.

162
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:01,190
What exactly happened?

163
00:06:01,190 --> 00:06:03,250
I wanted to hire a repair technician,

164
00:06:03,350 --> 00:06:05,320
but Xia Lei said he could do it.

165
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:09,810
I was also at fault.

166
00:06:10,030 --> 00:06:11,590
I believed him at the moment.

167
00:06:11,590 --> 00:06:12,620
He said he could fix it,

168
00:06:12,620 --> 00:06:13,980
so I let him try.

169
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:15,320
Wait, Ms. Zhao.

170
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:16,560
That's not true. You asked me to fix it.

171
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:18,280
Why are you making it sound like
I took the initiative?

172
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:19,190
Besides, when I went to fix it,

173
00:06:19,190 --> 00:06:20,510
the network had already been down.

174
00:06:20,510 --> 00:06:21,120
Xia Lei.

175
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,730
Can anyone prove what you said?

176
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:25,200
Meng Ge,

177
00:06:25,830 --> 00:06:26,830
When Meng Ge got off work,

178
00:06:26,830 --> 00:06:28,390
she saw us talking there.

179
00:06:29,670 --> 00:06:30,690
Go get Meng Ge.

180
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:31,530
Yes, Mr. Li.

181
00:06:33,980 --> 00:06:34,770
Meng Ge!

182
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,330
Mr. Li wants to see you. Come in.

183
00:06:42,530 --> 00:06:44,800
Meng Ge, explain to Mr. Li.

184
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,870
Didn't you see us talking

185
00:06:45,870 --> 00:06:47,240
out there yesterday?

186
00:06:48,390 --> 00:06:49,190
I did.

187
00:06:49,950 --> 00:06:50,600
Meng Ge.

188
00:06:51,630 --> 00:06:52,630
Did you hear that

189
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:55,120
Zhao asked Xia Lei

190
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,430
to repair the internet for her?

191
00:06:56,430 --> 00:06:58,460
I only heard something about
fixing the network.

192
00:06:58,460 --> 00:07:00,260
I'm not sure about the details.

193
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:04,640
You two can leave now.

194
00:07:04,770 --> 00:07:05,570
Xia Lei, stay.

195
00:07:10,870 --> 00:07:12,630
Mr. Li, no, that's not what happened.

196
00:07:12,630 --> 00:07:13,070
Sit.

197
00:07:14,630 --> 00:07:15,890
That was really scary.

198
00:07:16,630 --> 00:07:17,310
Xia Lei,

199
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:20,720
given your recent performance,

200
00:07:21,310 --> 00:07:22,270
I don't think

201
00:07:23,110 --> 00:07:24,970
you're a good fit for our company.

202
00:07:26,430 --> 00:07:27,800
No, Mr. Li. About the network,

203
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,860
it really isn't what it looks like...

204
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:32,440
I say you're not a good fit

205
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:35,120
not because you broke the company network,

206
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,500
but because you did things

207
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,770
outside your job description.

208
00:07:43,270 --> 00:07:44,870
I just wanted to help. I...

209
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:47,200
But someone has to take responsibility

210
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:49,600
for you overstepping your bounds, right?

211
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:53,960
Yes, you have the potential
to be a workhorse,

212
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:57,120
and you're willing to run errands
and help others.

213
00:07:58,490 --> 00:07:59,690
But on the other hand,

214
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:03,240
it's precisely because
you're willing to do anything

215
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:04,830
that I don't see

216
00:08:04,950 --> 00:08:06,610
any clear career goals in you.

217
00:08:11,170 --> 00:08:12,220
I... I have goals.

218
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:15,830
Then what are they?

219
00:08:20,140 --> 00:08:22,070
I want to stay and work in Shanghai.

220
00:08:24,490 --> 00:08:27,090
No, no, no. That doesn't count as
a career goal.

221
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,120
Anything you want to ask?

222
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:50,270
Go ahead.

223
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:54,360
I just don't understand

224
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:56,160
why you wouldn't testify for me.

225
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:00,520
Do you really think
me saying something in your defense

226
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:01,720
would have changed the outcome?

227
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:03,240
We're old classmates.

228
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,510
If you had said something in my defense,

229
00:09:04,510 --> 00:09:05,960
of course the outcome
would have been different.

230
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,220
As your old classmate,

231
00:09:07,670 --> 00:09:09,470
the first thing I want to tell you

232
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,080
is that your mistake was

233
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,670
taking on a task unrelated to you

234
00:09:12,670 --> 00:09:14,220
and then failing to see it through.

235
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:14,950
Secondly,

236
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,150
don't fool yourself into thinking

237
00:09:17,150 --> 00:09:19,280
all your colleagues are your friends,

238
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:21,030
and don't expect others to care about you

239
00:09:21,030 --> 00:09:23,160
more than they care about themselves.

240
00:09:23,950 --> 00:09:26,150
It's like this everywhere in the world.

241
00:09:28,380 --> 00:09:30,930
It was also like this
at the East Chemical Plant.

242
00:09:30,930 --> 00:09:32,460
You just didn't realize it.

243
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:34,200
But people in our plant say

244
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,910
"one for all, all for one."

245
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:38,480
That's our plant.
Things are different there.

246
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:40,550
That's a society based on
personal relationships.

247
00:09:40,550 --> 00:09:42,350
But the workplace runs on rules.

248
00:09:43,030 --> 00:09:45,030
I really don't know what I did wrong.

249
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:50,180
Doing more isn't necessarily right.

250
00:09:55,870 --> 00:09:57,670
What are you planning to do next?

251
00:09:58,630 --> 00:10:00,160
I'm tired. I want to go home.

252
00:10:02,650 --> 00:10:03,580
I'm leaving now.

253
00:10:26,630 --> 00:10:27,320
Have a soda.

254
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,100
Thanks, Boss Xiaoman.

255
00:10:32,980 --> 00:10:35,580
What boss?
We're all just working for a living.

256
00:10:38,150 --> 00:10:38,860
Chunchun.

257
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,670
You make so much in a day.

258
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,840
What do you want to do with it?

259
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:46,320
You run a dance hall
and sell clothes here.

260
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:49,320
Have I ever asked you
what you do with the money?

261
00:10:50,090 --> 00:10:50,780
No.

262
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:53,320
Then don't ask me either.

263
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,600
I'm just trying to make conversation,

264
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:56,200
and you just killed the vibe.

265
00:10:58,060 --> 00:10:59,270
Are you short of money?

266
00:10:59,270 --> 00:11:00,080
I am.

267
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:04,160
You know what, I've been short of money
since I was little.

268
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:06,360
When I was only about 10 years old,

269
00:11:06,530 --> 00:11:08,160
I was already helping my grandma
run a street stall,

270
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:09,360
selling cold dishes.

271
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:11,390
After that, we ran a newsstand.

272
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:13,550
And later, I delivered gas canisters.

273
00:11:13,550 --> 00:11:15,480
All because we were short of money.

274
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:19,490
So if there were a way
to make quick money,

275
00:11:19,490 --> 00:11:20,400
would you do it?

276
00:11:20,790 --> 00:11:21,850
I couldn't do that.

277
00:11:21,910 --> 00:11:23,640
I wouldn't feel right about it.

278
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,760
Why? You've done it before?

279
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:28,790
I tried working with them
for a couple of days,

280
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,360
but I couldn't keep at it.

281
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:35,640
Here's to your honesty and reliability.

282
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:44,020
How is it, Zhigang?

283
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,390
Look, it's only this hour,

284
00:11:45,390 --> 00:11:46,690
and there're already so many people here.

285
00:11:46,690 --> 00:11:47,210
Yes.

286
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:49,440
It's indeed much better than our place.

287
00:11:49,510 --> 00:11:50,120
So much better than

288
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:52,000
that leaky, broken shed of yours.

289
00:11:52,090 --> 00:11:54,520
We've got dozens of private karaoke rooms
here just for singing.

290
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:57,250
I'll take you to go wild
on the dance floor in a bit.

291
00:11:58,310 --> 00:11:59,030
Have fun.

292
00:11:59,240 --> 00:11:59,710
Bro.

293
00:12:01,430 --> 00:12:02,030
Look.

294
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:08,030
Awesome!

295
00:12:10,620 --> 00:12:12,790
Look, look.

296
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:14,780
Making money is just easy, right?

297
00:12:15,530 --> 00:12:17,300
Zhigang, you have to be flexible.

298
00:12:17,300 --> 00:12:19,700
Be flexible
and the money will come, right?

299
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:21,250
Boss Si.

300
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,630
Make this gentleman happy, got it?

301
00:12:22,630 --> 00:12:23,320
No problem.

302
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:25,510
This...

303
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:27,170
You know him?

304
00:12:27,510 --> 00:12:29,600
That guy comes to our place quite often.

305
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:30,790
Just you watch, Zhigang.

306
00:12:30,790 --> 00:12:31,480
All your customers

307
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:33,410
will end up coming over here
sooner or later.

308
00:12:33,410 --> 00:12:35,740
Let's go. Let's go wild
on the dance floor.

309
00:12:42,750 --> 00:12:43,790
I had to dance with people all night—

310
00:12:43,790 --> 00:12:45,300
do you think that makes me happy?

311
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:47,280
It's the middle of the night
and I'm out here alone.

312
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:49,210
Aren't you worried about me at all?

313
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:01,280
Chunchun.

314
00:13:03,630 --> 00:13:05,080
Here, have a Coke.

315
00:13:06,270 --> 00:13:08,130
You've been working hard lately.

316
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:11,060
It's nothing.
Just trying to make a living.

317
00:13:14,010 --> 00:13:14,510
Let me tell you,

318
00:13:14,510 --> 00:13:16,240
out of all you dance hostesses,

319
00:13:16,670 --> 00:13:18,200
you're the one I like the most.

320
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:18,750
Because I feel that

321
00:13:18,750 --> 00:13:20,720
you're fighting and working hard

322
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:22,220
for your dreams every day.

323
00:13:22,220 --> 00:13:24,190
You might as well just call me stupid.

324
00:13:24,190 --> 00:13:25,920
Not stupid at all. You're cute.

325
00:13:29,750 --> 00:13:30,870
Here's the thing.

326
00:13:30,870 --> 00:13:31,630
You see,

327
00:13:32,460 --> 00:13:33,680
I've got a job here

328
00:13:33,700 --> 00:13:35,230
that can make a lot of money.

329
00:13:35,790 --> 00:13:36,990
I'd like to cut you in.

330
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:38,830
What kind of job?

331
00:13:38,880 --> 00:13:39,940
The "cough syrup."

332
00:13:40,240 --> 00:13:41,200
When you're dancing,

333
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:43,600
just casually promote it to the customers.

334
00:13:44,870 --> 00:13:46,840
This is a dance hall, not a pharmacy.

335
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:47,940
How can we sell "cough syrup" here?

336
00:13:47,940 --> 00:13:48,790
Let me tell you,

337
00:13:48,790 --> 00:13:51,450
it's selling like hotcakes
at the Phoenix Dance Hall.

338
00:13:51,450 --> 00:13:53,440
How about this?
I'll give you commission.

339
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:55,440
50% for every bottle you sell.

340
00:13:55,550 --> 00:13:56,440
What do you think?

341
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:57,300
Look at you now,

342
00:13:57,630 --> 00:13:59,480
making peanuts from dancing.

343
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:01,000
What can you possibly do with that?

344
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,340
You're a person with dreams.

345
00:14:02,340 --> 00:14:03,910
Da and Nana said

346
00:14:03,940 --> 00:14:05,940
we can't sell this in our dance hall.

347
00:14:07,550 --> 00:14:10,170
Da and Nana are the bosses,

348
00:14:10,460 --> 00:14:11,180
but I'm not.

349
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:11,890
You are.

350
00:14:12,630 --> 00:14:14,360
The three of you are all bosses.

351
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:16,770
Then let us know
after you've agreed on it.

352
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:19,460
Did I say you could go?

353
00:14:19,460 --> 00:14:20,990
Did I say you could touch me?

354
00:14:29,750 --> 00:14:30,550
What's wrong?

355
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:31,980
What did Zhigang want with you?

356
00:14:31,980 --> 00:14:32,790
What else?

357
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:35,390
Giving instructions, of course.
Out of my way.

358
00:14:50,070 --> 00:14:51,800
Come on, get me a bottle of wine.

359
00:14:52,820 --> 00:14:54,550
Why did you wander in here again?

360
00:14:54,550 --> 00:14:55,670
Isn't your battery already fully charged?

361
00:14:55,670 --> 00:14:56,960
Here to steal electricity again?

362
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:58,500
I'm here to support my buddy's business.

363
00:14:58,500 --> 00:14:59,600
Why do you talk like that?

364
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,200
It really hurts my feelings.

365
00:15:01,220 --> 00:15:02,890
Besides, that's not stealing electricity.

366
00:15:02,890 --> 00:15:04,440
I'm just borrowing it temporarily, okay?

367
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:06,150
Just charge it at home for once.

368
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:07,610
Charging it here every day—

369
00:15:07,610 --> 00:15:08,610
have you no shame?

370
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:10,620
Not watching the shop anymore?

371
00:15:10,620 --> 00:15:11,950
Sun Lulu is watching it.

372
00:15:16,550 --> 00:15:18,150
Something's definitely up.

373
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:20,510
What is it?

374
00:15:21,670 --> 00:15:22,840
Zhigang probably wants to

375
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:24,350
secretly sell "cough syrup" here.

376
00:15:24,350 --> 00:15:26,080
I thought it was something big.

377
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,440
If he wants to sell, let him sell.

378
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:28,270
What's it got to do with you?

379
00:15:28,270 --> 00:15:28,840
Why so agitated?

380
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,550
He wants to sell it secretly.

381
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:32,450
Da must have no idea.

382
00:15:32,510 --> 00:15:33,720
You want to tell Da?

383
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:34,760
So what if I do?

384
00:15:34,870 --> 00:15:35,910
We are partners.

385
00:15:36,140 --> 00:15:36,870
You saw this,

386
00:15:36,870 --> 00:15:37,670
and you're not going to say anything?

387
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:38,610
Do you have proof?

388
00:15:38,610 --> 00:15:39,090
No.

389
00:15:39,270 --> 00:15:40,600
Then that's it.

390
00:15:41,550 --> 00:15:42,750
Why do I need proof?

391
00:15:43,270 --> 00:15:45,150
There're only a few of us here,
and the matter's clear.

392
00:15:45,150 --> 00:15:47,120
If we just lay it out and confront him,
what's he going to do, run away?

393
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:48,720
Why are you so eager

394
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:50,390
to make a scapegoat of yourself?

395
00:15:50,390 --> 00:15:51,720
With Zhigang's petty nature,

396
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:53,120
when he had that conflict with Da,

397
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:53,910
you supported Da.

398
00:15:53,910 --> 00:15:55,480
That was enough for him
to hold a grudge against you.

399
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:56,600
And now you want to

400
00:15:57,030 --> 00:15:58,480
take the initiative
to challenge him head-on?

401
00:15:58,480 --> 00:15:59,810
Are you out of your mind?

402
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:01,980
It doesn't matter if he holds a grudge.

403
00:16:01,980 --> 00:16:03,930
I'm not doing anything wrong.
I'm not afraid.

404
00:16:03,930 --> 00:16:05,320
Fine, fine, fine. You're not afraid.

405
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:06,080
But I am.

406
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:10,490
Xiaoman.

407
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:12,840
With the clothing business we're running,

408
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,440
I wouldn't say it's booming—

409
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:17,070
but at least we're making a bit of money
every day,

410
00:16:17,070 --> 00:16:17,670
right?

411
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:19,520
Compared to Zhigang,

412
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:21,010
he has nothing to lose,

413
00:16:21,030 --> 00:16:22,550
but you do.

414
00:16:22,810 --> 00:16:23,870
So it's okay to be a little afraid.

415
00:16:23,870 --> 00:16:25,400
I've got something to lose?

416
00:16:25,630 --> 00:16:26,870
What is it?

417
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:29,480
We've been stuck here for months,

418
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:31,140
with just a few hundred bucks.

419
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:33,000
And our clothing business—

420
00:16:33,730 --> 00:16:35,270
right, it's been selling well recently,

421
00:16:35,270 --> 00:16:36,820
but aren't we still operating at a loss?

422
00:16:36,820 --> 00:16:37,360
You know

423
00:16:37,390 --> 00:16:38,360
I've been saving up for a mobile phone,

424
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:39,150
but I've been saving for so long,

425
00:16:39,150 --> 00:16:40,390
and I still can't afford it.

426
00:16:40,390 --> 00:16:42,880
It's such a hassle
to contact Xiaodan every day.

427
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:44,360
That money's only tied up

428
00:16:44,870 --> 00:16:46,790
because I went to the wholesale market
to get a batch of top-notch goods

429
00:16:46,790 --> 00:16:48,050
a while back, you know?

430
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:49,360
Just wait until we sell the stock.

431
00:16:49,360 --> 00:16:51,910
Once we make the profit, the two of us
can spend it however we want, go all out.

432
00:16:51,910 --> 00:16:52,980
Look at you.

433
00:16:53,550 --> 00:16:54,550
Give me a break.

434
00:16:54,550 --> 00:16:55,630
If I believed you,

435
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:57,190
I'd have become an immortal by now.

436
00:16:57,190 --> 00:16:58,190
Listen to me.

437
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:01,510
From now on, we'll just have

438
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:04,780
a business partnership
with the dance hall.

439
00:17:05,030 --> 00:17:07,750
Don't get involved in
their internal affairs anymore.

440
00:17:07,750 --> 00:17:09,010
Wait, what do you mean?

441
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:11,680
They opened this dance hall,

442
00:17:12,450 --> 00:17:13,270
and just when they need a push,

443
00:17:13,270 --> 00:17:14,270
you stop helping?

444
00:17:14,270 --> 00:17:16,270
Isn't that like pulling the bricks
halfway through building a house?

445
00:17:16,270 --> 00:17:18,329
Anyway, you just can't say anything.

446
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:19,640
If you say something now,

447
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:20,349
crack—

448
00:17:20,890 --> 00:17:22,170
it'll all collapse.

449
00:17:22,410 --> 00:17:23,000
Be good.

450
00:17:27,270 --> 00:17:27,680
Do you hear me?

451
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:28,830
Stop kicking me.

452
00:17:28,950 --> 00:17:30,680
You're really full of schemes.

453
00:17:31,030 --> 00:17:32,410
What do you want to drink?
I'll get it for you.

454
00:17:32,410 --> 00:17:33,140
German beer.

455
00:17:33,980 --> 00:17:34,870
German?

456
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:37,530
You can't even handle the local stuff.

457
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,470
How about it? Want to dance one more song?

458
00:17:40,470 --> 00:17:41,200
I think I'll pass.

459
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,110
I've danced 3 songs already.

460
00:17:42,110 --> 00:17:43,040
I'm heading out.

461
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:44,720
Come on, just one more.

462
00:17:44,850 --> 00:17:45,830
It's on me.

463
00:17:45,830 --> 00:17:47,590
Dancing with you is the easiest.

464
00:17:47,590 --> 00:17:48,200
Let's go.

465
00:17:49,140 --> 00:17:50,540
Why are you looking at me?

466
00:17:50,550 --> 00:17:51,880
Did my eyelash fall off?

467
00:17:52,270 --> 00:17:53,480
No, I really have something to do today.

468
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,160
I have to go.

469
00:18:01,610 --> 00:18:02,140
Hey, you!

470
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:03,020
Taking a break?

471
00:18:03,490 --> 00:18:05,550
That old man kept stepping on my feet.

472
00:18:36,850 --> 00:18:38,640
Hello, this is the Workers' Dance Hall.

473
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:39,480
Hello.

474
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:41,080
I'd like to speak to Xiaoman.

475
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:42,250
Alright.

476
00:18:42,280 --> 00:18:43,530
Want to talk to Xiaoman, right?
Just a moment.

477
00:18:43,530 --> 00:18:44,230
Xiaoman!

478
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:45,830
Someone's on the phone for you.

479
00:18:45,830 --> 00:18:46,440
Who is it?

480
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:47,870
The voice sounds strange.

481
00:18:47,870 --> 00:18:48,790
Can't tell whether it's a man or a woman.

482
00:18:48,790 --> 00:18:49,400
Coming.

483
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:52,790
Hello?

484
00:18:54,310 --> 00:18:55,000
Hello?

485
00:18:55,410 --> 00:18:56,160
Is that Xiaoman?

486
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:56,820
Who's this?

487
00:18:57,310 --> 00:18:57,920
It's me.

488
00:18:59,350 --> 00:19:00,070
Dongdong?

489
00:19:01,590 --> 00:19:02,310
No.

490
00:19:02,830 --> 00:19:03,830
Then who? Xia Lei?

491
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:05,460
No, not him either.

492
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:06,690
Guess again.

493
00:19:07,350 --> 00:19:08,030
Mr. Ding?

494
00:19:09,090 --> 00:19:10,220
What's up, Mr. Ding?

495
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:12,030
Wrong again.

496
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:14,610
Then why did you respond like that?

497
00:19:14,750 --> 00:19:15,410
Who's this?

498
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:16,310
Xiaoman,

499
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:17,790
it's me.

500
00:19:18,750 --> 00:19:19,550
Zhuang Sen?

501
00:19:20,790 --> 00:19:21,720
Why are you

502
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:23,490
playing games with me
in the middle of the night?

503
00:19:23,490 --> 00:19:24,490
Just teasing you.

504
00:19:25,220 --> 00:19:27,000
I picked up a mobile phone
in the dance hall.

505
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,030
Then hurry up and bring it back.

506
00:19:28,030 --> 00:19:29,290
What if the owner comes looking for it?

507
00:19:29,290 --> 00:19:31,720
If the owner really comes looking for it,
I'll give it back then.

508
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:32,810
What's wrong with having some fun first?

509
00:19:32,810 --> 00:19:34,400
You've really got too much time
on your hands. Have fun by yourself.

510
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:35,800
I'm getting back to work.

511
00:19:40,860 --> 00:19:41,720
He hung up on me.

512
00:19:42,180 --> 00:19:44,340
Time to get off work. Let's go.

513
00:19:46,060 --> 00:19:48,060
It's really cooled down, hasn't it?

514
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:50,510
Nana, did you hear anyone say
they lost their phone

515
00:19:50,510 --> 00:19:51,170
here today?

516
00:19:52,810 --> 00:19:54,110
I'll ask around tomorrow.

517
00:19:54,110 --> 00:19:54,590
Okay.

518
00:19:54,590 --> 00:19:56,650
Let's check when we come in tomorrow.

519
00:20:29,030 --> 00:20:29,720
Hello.

520
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:31,070
Who are you looking for?

521
00:20:31,070 --> 00:20:33,000
Where's the person in charge here?

522
00:20:33,150 --> 00:20:33,740
Not here.

523
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:35,420
What's wrong? You can tell me.

524
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:43,770
We're from
Tiecheng Public Security Bureau.

525
00:20:44,020 --> 00:20:45,690
Last night at 11:47 PM,

526
00:20:45,810 --> 00:20:46,980
who called here?

527
00:20:49,880 --> 00:20:50,680
No one called.

528
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:52,810
Think carefully before you answer me.

529
00:20:54,270 --> 00:20:55,070
Who called...

530
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:58,000
Well, um...

531
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:58,640
Well... Well...

532
00:20:58,640 --> 00:20:59,400
Sen called.

533
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:00,240
Who's Sen?

534
00:21:01,350 --> 00:21:02,160
My partner.

535
00:21:02,270 --> 00:21:02,930
Where is he?

536
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:06,570
Probably sleeping in the caravan.

537
00:21:06,650 --> 00:21:07,450
Take me there.

538
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:09,440
Wait...

539
00:21:10,030 --> 00:21:11,290
What... What did he do?

540
00:21:11,540 --> 00:21:12,400
What happened?

541
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:18,590
Sen.

542
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:20,030
Sen!

543
00:21:21,270 --> 00:21:22,480
So he's Sen, right?

544
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:25,480
Wait.

545
00:21:25,870 --> 00:21:26,960
-What are you doing?
-Don't move!

546
00:21:26,960 --> 00:21:27,310
God.

547
00:21:27,690 --> 00:21:28,480
-Zhuang, you...
-Freeze!

548
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:29,720
-Handcuff him.
-What did he do?

549
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:30,160
Handcuff him.

550
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:30,880
What did you do?

551
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:32,400
Officer, I didn't do anything!

552
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:32,880
Wait...

553
00:21:32,920 --> 00:21:33,720
Xiaoman!

554
00:21:34,030 --> 00:21:34,890
What happened?

555
00:21:35,990 --> 00:21:37,550
Wait, explain to the police

556
00:21:37,550 --> 00:21:38,350
that I didn't do anything!

557
00:21:38,350 --> 00:21:38,790
Wait, wait...

558
00:21:38,790 --> 00:21:40,070
I'm just a vendor.

559
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:41,270
Hey! Xiaoman!

560
00:21:41,270 --> 00:21:42,160
What did you do?

561
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:43,590
I didn't do anything!

562
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:44,750
This must be a misunderstanding!

563
00:21:44,750 --> 00:21:45,550
Easy, please!

564
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:46,410
Xiaoman!

565
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:47,800
Then I... Can I come with him?

566
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:49,000
I still have my stall!

567
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:49,960
Xiaoman!

568
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:51,110
What did you do?

569
00:21:51,110 --> 00:21:52,590
Explain it to the police!

570
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:54,510
I didn't do anything!

571
00:21:56,110 --> 00:21:56,720
Xiaoman!

572
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,130
This... This...

573
00:22:01,030 --> 00:22:02,630
I really didn't do anything!

574
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:05,180
Watch the stall! Wait for me to come back!

575
00:22:09,350 --> 00:22:10,060
Da!

576
00:22:11,350 --> 00:22:12,110
Where is Da?

577
00:22:13,270 --> 00:22:14,670
Zhuang Sen was arrested!

578
00:22:20,990 --> 00:22:21,600
Xiaoman.

579
00:22:22,110 --> 00:22:23,510
Do you think Chunchun's dance partner

580
00:22:23,510 --> 00:22:24,680
likes her?

581
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,600
He picks her every time he comes.

582
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:29,940
Watch the place.

583
00:22:29,940 --> 00:22:30,830
I'm going to the public security bureau.

584
00:22:30,830 --> 00:22:31,350
What for?

585
00:22:31,350 --> 00:22:32,470
Sit... Sit here.

586
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:34,600
Why are you being so anxious?

587
00:22:35,350 --> 00:22:37,350
He'll be out once he explains things
clearly to the police.

588
00:22:37,350 --> 00:22:38,350
Just s-sit here.

589
00:22:38,350 --> 00:22:40,550
It's been so long.
Why hasn't he finished explaining?

590
00:22:40,550 --> 00:22:41,880
Why worry?

591
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:44,260
With Zhuang Cent's little nerve,

592
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:45,960
he could barely even
steal some electricity.

593
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:47,070
A criminal case?

594
00:22:47,070 --> 00:22:47,930
Give me a break.

595
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:48,550
Just sit tight.

596
00:22:48,550 --> 00:22:50,510
But I can't just wait here.

597
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:51,410
Don't worry.

598
00:22:57,510 --> 00:22:58,160
Want one?

599
00:22:58,350 --> 00:22:59,200
I don't smoke.

600
00:23:01,010 --> 00:23:03,810
It's rare to see a guy
who doesn't smoke these days.

601
00:23:04,310 --> 00:23:05,880
Isn't smoking bad for health?

602
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:07,140
You'd better quit too.

603
00:23:08,360 --> 00:23:09,690
There're plenty of bad things
in this world.

604
00:23:09,690 --> 00:23:11,350
Being a dance hostess is also bad.

605
00:23:11,350 --> 00:23:12,610
Should I quit that too?

606
00:23:13,220 --> 00:23:15,550
So you actually see things quite clearly.

607
00:23:15,660 --> 00:23:17,060
It's truly not that good.

608
00:23:17,070 --> 00:23:18,310
Look, you're so young.

609
00:23:18,310 --> 00:23:20,040
Why don't you find a decent job?

610
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:22,480
Just say it if you want to
dance with someone else.

611
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:24,140
No need to ruin my livelihood.

612
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:25,880
Look, I didn't mean that.

613
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:27,880
I just wanted to say

614
00:23:27,880 --> 00:23:30,350
that you're still young and able-bodied.

615
00:23:30,350 --> 00:23:31,350
Find a proper job—

616
00:23:31,510 --> 00:23:33,240
like a waitress, right?

617
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:34,440
Even that's better than
being a dance hostess.

618
00:23:34,440 --> 00:23:36,370
I've danced with you so many times.

619
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:37,480
You should know

620
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:38,790
that I dance decently

621
00:23:38,790 --> 00:23:40,720
and don't get involved in
any shady business.

622
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:42,000
What's shameful about that?

623
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:42,640
Right.

624
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:43,920
I know that, of course.

625
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:45,850
Because we know each other so well.

626
00:23:46,180 --> 00:23:48,160
The problem is that others don't know.

627
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:48,920
If your relatives

628
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:50,440
found out about this,

629
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:51,240
how would you face them?

630
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:52,650
Are you crazy or something?

631
00:23:52,650 --> 00:23:54,070
Look, I'm just concerned about you.

632
00:23:54,070 --> 00:23:55,400
Why are you getting mad?

633
00:23:58,070 --> 00:23:59,720
I heard my friends say

634
00:24:00,350 --> 00:24:02,080
that men have two main hobbies:

635
00:24:02,650 --> 00:24:04,400
dragging decent women into the mire,

636
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:06,680
and persuading prostitutes
to turn over a new leaf.

637
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:07,830
I didn't expect

638
00:24:07,960 --> 00:24:09,890
to run into a living example today.

639
00:24:11,750 --> 00:24:13,110
I just picked up a mobile phone,
and the police questioned me for ages.

640
00:24:13,110 --> 00:24:15,240
It's a relief that everything's okay.

641
00:24:19,790 --> 00:24:20,400
Wait.

642
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:24,250
Something's not right.

643
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:27,960
Where are you?

644
00:24:28,520 --> 00:24:29,000
Got it.

645
00:24:29,030 --> 00:24:29,880
Just wait there...

646
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:31,240
I need to borrow your phone.

647
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:32,510
Why did you snatch my phone?

648
00:24:32,510 --> 00:24:33,310
Get back here!

649
00:24:34,460 --> 00:24:35,660
Bro, stop chasing me!

650
00:24:36,090 --> 00:24:36,890
It's urgent!

651
00:24:36,910 --> 00:24:38,300
Of course I have to chase you!

652
00:24:38,300 --> 00:24:39,300
You took my phone!

653
00:24:43,030 --> 00:24:43,830
Stop chasing me...

654
00:24:43,830 --> 00:24:44,680
Hello? Hello?

655
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:46,550
Pick up the phone!

656
00:24:49,250 --> 00:24:49,820
Hello?

657
00:24:50,640 --> 00:24:51,170
Xiaoman!

658
00:24:51,270 --> 00:24:51,830
Xiaoman!

659
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:53,350
Xiaoman!

660
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:56,010
There's a murderer!

661
00:24:56,880 --> 00:24:57,350
Murderer?

662
00:24:57,350 --> 00:24:58,260
There's a murderer.

663
00:24:58,260 --> 00:24:59,070
Let me tell you—

664
00:24:59,070 --> 00:25:00,790
that gigolo
who always dances with Chunchun,

665
00:25:00,790 --> 00:25:01,990
the one with glasses—

666
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,660
he's from the Hammer Gang!

667
00:25:05,990 --> 00:25:06,850
Sen is okay now.

668
00:25:07,070 --> 00:25:07,720
He's okay?

669
00:25:07,830 --> 00:25:09,090
That mobile phone he picked up

670
00:25:09,090 --> 00:25:11,110
was previously snatched
by the Hammer Gang.

671
00:25:11,110 --> 00:25:12,640
That guy's one of the Hammer Gang members.

672
00:25:12,640 --> 00:25:13,310
Which guy?

673
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:17,220
Where's Chunchun?

674
00:25:17,880 --> 00:25:20,010
No idea. She was still here a while ago.

675
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:21,570
I'm telling you,

676
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:24,550
I'm a dance hostess,

677
00:25:25,090 --> 00:25:26,370
not a prostitute.

678
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:30,000
Mind your own business,

679
00:25:30,550 --> 00:25:31,640
or I'll slap you.

680
00:25:32,830 --> 00:25:33,510
Let go!

681
00:25:33,880 --> 00:25:34,480
Let go!

682
00:25:34,680 --> 00:25:36,030
Are you crazy or what?

683
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:42,300
Stop following me.

684
00:25:44,030 --> 00:25:44,880
-I...
-You...

685
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:46,590
Get over here!

686
00:25:46,590 --> 00:25:47,650
Don't make a sound!

687
00:25:49,040 --> 00:25:50,100
Don't make a sound!

688
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:51,200
Help!

689
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:51,790
Stop it.

690
00:25:52,750 --> 00:25:53,310
Shut up!

691
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:54,260
Someone, help!

692
00:25:56,310 --> 00:25:57,070
You pervert!

693
00:25:57,590 --> 00:25:58,110
Freeze!

694
00:25:58,350 --> 00:25:59,010
Don't move!

695
00:25:59,510 --> 00:26:00,550
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

696
00:26:00,550 --> 00:26:01,080
I'm okay.

697
00:26:01,090 --> 00:26:01,520
Here.

698
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:02,830
-Let go.
-Still talking back?

699
00:26:02,830 --> 00:26:04,790
-You wretch...
-Let me see you talk like that now!

700
00:26:04,790 --> 00:26:05,350
Xiaoman!

701
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:06,960
Da!

702
00:26:06,960 --> 00:26:08,110
-What happened?
-Bro.

703
00:26:08,110 --> 00:26:09,270
It's the Hammer Gang!

704
00:26:09,270 --> 00:26:10,240
He's from the Hammer Gang.

705
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:12,030
He just tried to hammer Chunchun.

706
00:26:12,030 --> 00:26:12,830
Nana, call the police!

707
00:26:12,830 --> 00:26:13,350
Okay.

708
00:26:14,510 --> 00:26:15,090
What's going on?

709
00:26:15,090 --> 00:26:15,750
No idea.

710
00:26:19,050 --> 00:26:19,910
Move! Hurry up.

711
00:26:21,350 --> 00:26:22,150
Captain Feng.

712
00:26:22,500 --> 00:26:23,500
Thank you so much.

713
00:26:23,550 --> 00:26:25,350
I should be the one thanking you.

714
00:26:25,750 --> 00:26:28,270
Not only for your bravery

715
00:26:28,270 --> 00:26:29,790
in helping us catch the criminal,

716
00:26:29,790 --> 00:26:30,750
but seeing you

717
00:26:30,890 --> 00:26:33,000
running your business honestly

718
00:26:33,410 --> 00:26:34,270
also puts my mind at ease.

719
00:26:34,270 --> 00:26:35,480
That's what we should do.

720
00:26:35,480 --> 00:26:36,070
In this area,

721
00:26:36,070 --> 00:26:37,240
there's absolutely no place

722
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:38,510
cleaner than our dance hall.

723
00:26:38,510 --> 00:26:40,270
Who's the one that hit him just now?

724
00:26:40,270 --> 00:26:41,510
That was quite a brutal beating.

725
00:26:41,510 --> 00:26:42,750
C-Can't you tell?

726
00:26:43,030 --> 00:26:43,960
It was Chunchun.

727
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:47,480
You did that, Chunchun?

728
00:26:47,960 --> 00:26:49,020
My apologies for underestimating you.

729
00:26:49,020 --> 00:26:50,880
This girl here is something else.

730
00:26:51,310 --> 00:26:53,000
Don't let this guy's glasses fool you.

731
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:54,060
He may look gentle,

732
00:26:55,110 --> 00:26:56,480
but he's taken several lives.

733
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:57,110
Really?

734
00:26:57,700 --> 00:26:58,960
That's it for now then.

735
00:26:59,860 --> 00:27:01,260
Take care, Captain Feng.

736
00:27:02,200 --> 00:27:03,370
-He killed several people?
-Let's go.

737
00:27:03,370 --> 00:27:03,900
Let's go.

738
00:27:04,920 --> 00:27:06,400
Go home early and get some rest.

739
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:07,240
That was brutal just now.

740
00:27:07,240 --> 00:27:08,170
Did you get hurt?

741
00:27:08,640 --> 00:27:09,640
No.

742
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:10,750
That was nothing.

743
00:27:10,750 --> 00:27:12,550
My dad used to beat me way harder.

744
00:27:13,030 --> 00:27:13,920
Look at you.

745
00:27:15,350 --> 00:27:16,400
That was terrifying.

746
00:27:16,400 --> 00:27:17,310
He's killed several people—

747
00:27:17,310 --> 00:27:18,070
you heard that?

748
00:27:18,070 --> 00:27:18,510
Yeah.

749
00:27:18,510 --> 00:27:20,440
Just thinking about it now
still scares me.

750
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:22,720
Thank you guys for today.

751
00:27:23,070 --> 00:27:24,090
Otherwise...

752
00:27:24,200 --> 00:27:25,160
Don't mention it.

753
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:25,800
I'm telling you,

754
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:27,550
people from our plant are the most united.

755
00:27:27,550 --> 00:27:29,480
There's no way we wouldn't step in
something like this.

756
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:30,920
Besides, you're here with us.

757
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:31,750
How could we let anything happen to you?

758
00:27:31,750 --> 00:27:33,210
That would be ridiculous.

759
00:27:35,980 --> 00:27:38,380
So horrifying. My heart is still pounding.

760
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:54,030
Cui.

761
00:27:54,310 --> 00:27:55,470
What's wrong with you?

762
00:27:55,470 --> 00:27:57,190
Go away. Don't pry.

763
00:27:59,070 --> 00:28:00,510
Why are you getting mad?

764
00:28:02,440 --> 00:28:03,030
Tieda!

765
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:05,350
Mr. Cui.

766
00:28:05,720 --> 00:28:06,520
Get down here!

767
00:28:08,370 --> 00:28:09,770
Talk to him nicely, okay?

768
00:28:09,830 --> 00:28:10,890
Alright, alright.

769
00:28:14,160 --> 00:28:15,290
What can I do for you?

770
00:28:16,960 --> 00:28:18,440
I'm done dancing. No fun.

771
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:21,440
What's wrong? Who pissed you off?

772
00:28:22,310 --> 00:28:23,570
Tieda, let me tell you.

773
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:25,240
When I came here on your opening day,

774
00:28:25,240 --> 00:28:26,680
I was very, very happy,

775
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:27,400
you know?

776
00:28:27,530 --> 00:28:29,350
At least there was a dance hall like this

777
00:28:29,350 --> 00:28:31,550
that could give us old-school dancers

778
00:28:31,550 --> 00:28:32,590
a place to belong.

779
00:28:33,360 --> 00:28:34,620
But you guys always...

780
00:28:36,030 --> 00:28:37,030
Well, I get it,

781
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:39,350
it's all about the market economy
these days.

782
00:28:39,350 --> 00:28:41,310
Your dance hall needs to make money too,

783
00:28:41,310 --> 00:28:41,960
right?

784
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:44,480
But if you keep doing business like this,

785
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:46,000
it's no longer suitable for people like us

786
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:46,880
to dance here.

787
00:28:47,480 --> 00:28:48,010
Let's go.

788
00:28:48,320 --> 00:28:48,850
Get up!

789
00:28:48,880 --> 00:28:50,530
Mr. Cui, please, make yourself clear.

790
00:28:50,530 --> 00:28:52,000
You're not someone
who beats around the bush.

791
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:53,070
Just say it straight. What's wrong?

792
00:28:53,070 --> 00:28:54,270
Who upset that baldy?

793
00:28:54,270 --> 00:28:56,070
Who knows? Who would dare upset him?

794
00:28:56,070 --> 00:28:57,240
You really want me to tell the truth, huh?

795
00:28:57,240 --> 00:28:58,310
Yeah, say it. Straight out.

796
00:28:58,310 --> 00:28:59,370
Then I'll tell you.

797
00:29:00,160 --> 00:29:01,310
No matter what you sell here,

798
00:29:01,310 --> 00:29:03,490
you can't be selling
that "cough syrup."

799
00:29:03,490 --> 00:29:05,660
There's no way we sell that stuff here.

800
00:29:05,690 --> 00:29:07,030
I've warned everyone

801
00:29:07,030 --> 00:29:08,720
that we don't sell that kind of
shady stuff here.

802
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:09,920
Why would I lie to you?

803
00:29:10,030 --> 00:29:12,090
When I went to the men's room just now,

804
00:29:12,640 --> 00:29:14,440
that woman—that one right over there—

805
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:16,300
was selling "cough syrup" there.

806
00:29:16,590 --> 00:29:17,550
She even said things like,

807
00:29:17,550 --> 00:29:19,350
"this stuff not only gives you a kick,

808
00:29:19,350 --> 00:29:20,000
you know?

809
00:29:20,110 --> 00:29:21,350
If you drink a whole bottle,

810
00:29:21,350 --> 00:29:22,790
you won't need to go to the toilet
all night."

811
00:29:22,790 --> 00:29:24,720
Wouldn't that just make you burst?

812
00:29:30,470 --> 00:29:31,160
Nana!

813
00:29:32,070 --> 00:29:34,130
Call all the dance hostesses up here!

814
00:29:35,880 --> 00:29:37,080
You guys, come up too.

815
00:29:39,550 --> 00:29:40,480
What's going on?

816
00:29:40,530 --> 00:29:44,190
-The customers are waiting.
-Nothing to do with you. Stand aside.

817
00:29:48,290 --> 00:29:50,290
Who among you is selling drugs here?

818
00:29:53,030 --> 00:29:54,290
I'll ask one more time:

819
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:57,200
who among you is selling drugs here?

820
00:30:07,450 --> 00:30:08,250
Jiajia!

821
00:30:15,920 --> 00:30:17,180
Who gave you the drugs?

822
00:30:17,270 --> 00:30:18,070
Don't be afraid.

823
00:30:18,070 --> 00:30:19,530
Just tell us what you know.

824
00:30:19,680 --> 00:30:20,600
I don't know.

825
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:22,860
Was it Wei Si who gave it to you?

826
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:25,350
I'm asking you!

827
00:30:25,540 --> 00:30:26,800
Why do you have to yell?

828
00:30:26,880 --> 00:30:27,640
The customers are all waiting downstairs.

829
00:30:27,640 --> 00:30:28,830
Why can't I yell at her?

830
00:30:28,830 --> 00:30:29,720
What have you been doing?

831
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:30,480
Is she one of your girls or not?

832
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:32,270
I'm here managing dance hostesses,

833
00:30:32,270 --> 00:30:33,550
purchasing, and doing accounts all day!

834
00:30:33,550 --> 00:30:34,000
How can I possibly handle everything...

835
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:35,350
Can you stop arguing with me?

836
00:30:35,350 --> 00:30:36,110
Are you done yet?

837
00:30:36,110 --> 00:30:37,570
I dare you to keep yelling!

838
00:30:39,830 --> 00:30:40,890
Get her out of here.

839
00:30:41,710 --> 00:30:43,640
Make her get the hell out right now.

840
00:30:43,990 --> 00:30:45,850
Settle this month's pay with her.

841
00:30:50,310 --> 00:30:51,170
Do you hear him?

842
00:30:51,720 --> 00:30:52,600
Everyone.

843
00:30:54,220 --> 00:30:55,750
I'll say this one last time.

844
00:30:56,160 --> 00:30:58,560
If anyone ever dares
sell drugs here again,

845
00:31:00,240 --> 00:31:02,750
it won't be so simple as
just getting the hell out.

846
00:31:02,750 --> 00:31:03,750
Did you hear that?

847
00:31:04,590 --> 00:31:05,720
Are you mute or what!

848
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:07,030
We heard that.

849
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:07,960
Let's go.

850
00:31:14,270 --> 00:31:15,400
Move. Go on.

851
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:16,640
Move.

852
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:18,510
Hurry up.

853
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:20,400
Move faster, you all!

854
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:21,440
Stop dawdling!

855
00:31:29,650 --> 00:31:30,580
Why pull me here?

856
00:31:31,590 --> 00:31:33,510
If he really wanted to know
who was selling drugs,

857
00:31:33,510 --> 00:31:35,400
he wouldn't have held a meeting here.

858
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:37,200
He'd have just asked in private.

859
00:31:39,070 --> 00:31:40,270
So what did that mean?

860
00:31:40,350 --> 00:31:41,680
What else could it mean?

861
00:31:42,750 --> 00:31:44,810
He was trying to warn certain people.

862
00:31:50,840 --> 00:31:51,320
Bro.

863
00:31:51,440 --> 00:31:52,240
Zhigang!

864
00:31:52,350 --> 00:31:53,440
Come here.

865
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:54,590
Come on, sit.

866
00:31:55,050 --> 00:31:55,910
Bring the wine.

867
00:31:58,040 --> 00:31:58,700
And a glass.

868
00:32:01,290 --> 00:32:03,180
Come on, my dear friend.

869
00:32:03,650 --> 00:32:05,180
You finally remembered me?

870
00:32:05,790 --> 00:32:07,320
Come on, let's have a drink.

871
00:32:10,680 --> 00:32:11,540
How has it been?

872
00:32:11,750 --> 00:32:13,110
Selling well, right?

873
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:16,140
I just started selling it,

874
00:32:16,310 --> 00:32:17,790
and Da found out.

875
00:32:18,630 --> 00:32:20,230
He fired that dance hostess.

876
00:32:21,240 --> 00:32:21,900
Therefore,

877
00:32:22,070 --> 00:32:23,960
bro, I came here today
to talk to you about something.

878
00:32:23,960 --> 00:32:24,820
I was wondering

879
00:32:24,830 --> 00:32:25,960
if you could

880
00:32:27,230 --> 00:32:28,560
lend me a couple of guys.

881
00:32:28,710 --> 00:32:30,230
If he won't let me make money,

882
00:32:30,230 --> 00:32:32,090
I won't let him have peace either.

883
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:35,520
Li, do this. Go ask Liu

884
00:32:35,550 --> 00:32:36,940
to come and keep Zhigang here company.

885
00:32:36,940 --> 00:32:37,460
Go on.

886
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:44,030
Zhigang.

887
00:32:46,110 --> 00:32:47,790
Venting your anger for you

888
00:32:47,790 --> 00:32:49,510
is no problem. That's a trivial matter.

889
00:32:49,510 --> 00:32:50,890
I'll just ask some men

890
00:32:50,910 --> 00:32:52,040
to go stir things up,

891
00:32:52,350 --> 00:32:52,920
right?

892
00:32:53,160 --> 00:32:54,680
But you know what our problem is
right now?

893
00:32:54,680 --> 00:32:56,270
We need to figure out a way

894
00:32:56,830 --> 00:32:58,030
to keep this business

895
00:32:58,030 --> 00:32:59,110
running in the Workers' Dance Hall.

896
00:32:59,110 --> 00:33:00,550
It has to keep going.

897
00:33:00,750 --> 00:33:03,240
Bro, as long as no one snitches,

898
00:33:03,720 --> 00:33:04,480
I'm sure—

899
00:33:04,480 --> 00:33:07,340
absolutely sure—
that there won't be any problems.

900
00:33:08,050 --> 00:33:10,180
Bro, I can't say

901
00:33:10,210 --> 00:33:11,560
your idea is wrong,

902
00:33:13,880 --> 00:33:15,610
but you're thinking too small.

903
00:33:15,790 --> 00:33:18,490
Do you know what kind of mindset
you're in right now?

904
00:33:18,490 --> 00:33:21,350
It's like you're
living under someone else's roof.

905
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:23,000
You have to become strong yourself

906
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:24,510
and strike out on your own.

907
00:33:24,870 --> 00:33:27,080
That way, you won't have to
rely on their whims.

908
00:33:27,080 --> 00:33:28,540
Think about it, am I right?

909
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:39,130
I called you all here for a meeting.
Nothing serious.

910
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:42,740
It's just our dance hall
has been doing really well lately,

911
00:33:42,740 --> 00:33:45,270
so I want to give everyone
a share of the bonus.

912
00:33:47,590 --> 00:33:48,120
Zhigang.

913
00:33:48,790 --> 00:33:49,500
Thanks, bro.

914
00:33:49,500 --> 00:33:50,430
Xiaoman, yours.

915
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:51,360
Thanks, bro.

916
00:33:53,400 --> 00:33:54,130
My goodness.

917
00:33:54,980 --> 00:33:55,690
This is great.

918
00:33:55,690 --> 00:33:57,480
I'll go get my mobile phone set in a bit.

919
00:33:57,480 --> 00:33:58,540
What mobile phone?

920
00:33:58,590 --> 00:33:59,790
I'm buying a mobile phone.

921
00:33:59,790 --> 00:34:01,240
Getting myself equipped.

922
00:34:01,240 --> 00:34:02,300
Alright, alright.

923
00:34:02,790 --> 00:34:04,990
Looks like you've made money out there—

924
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:06,110
that clothing stall.

925
00:34:06,110 --> 00:34:07,770
I knew it, you've been putting

926
00:34:08,060 --> 00:34:09,030
all your focus out there.

927
00:34:09,030 --> 00:34:10,130
What are you talking about?

928
00:34:10,130 --> 00:34:11,469
Sen and I

929
00:34:11,489 --> 00:34:13,320
just want to make some clean money,

930
00:34:13,320 --> 00:34:13,880
you know?

931
00:34:13,900 --> 00:34:16,370
Alright. Everyone has been
working pretty hard lately,

932
00:34:16,370 --> 00:34:17,500
so the bonuses are quite generous.

933
00:34:17,500 --> 00:34:18,300
Keep it up.

934
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:20,760
Our dance hall's business
will surely keep booming.

935
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:21,880
-Got it.
-No problem.

936
00:34:21,880 --> 00:34:22,510
We will.

937
00:34:23,030 --> 00:34:23,630
Come on.

938
00:34:25,150 --> 00:34:26,110
I'm getting back to work.

939
00:34:26,110 --> 00:34:27,040
Go on, everyone.

940
00:34:27,670 --> 00:34:28,920
Don't spend it recklessly.

941
00:34:28,920 --> 00:34:30,110
Let's chip in for a flip phone.

942
00:34:30,110 --> 00:34:30,710
We can take turns using it
every other day.

943
00:34:30,710 --> 00:34:31,800
I'll pass. I'm not buying one.

944
00:34:31,800 --> 00:34:32,469
Come on, let's get a mobile phone.

945
00:34:32,469 --> 00:34:32,969
No, I'll pass.

946
00:34:32,969 --> 00:34:34,370
Don't you make phone calls?

947
00:34:34,370 --> 00:34:34,889
I don't.

948
00:34:37,630 --> 00:34:38,560
Are we done here?

949
00:34:39,070 --> 00:34:39,710
Yeah.

950
00:35:03,510 --> 00:35:04,070
Hello?

951
00:35:04,630 --> 00:35:05,280
Hello?

952
00:35:05,550 --> 00:35:06,110
Hello?

953
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:07,770
Is that Xiaodan?

954
00:35:07,850 --> 00:35:08,930
Guess who this is.

955
00:35:09,710 --> 00:35:10,510
Xiaoman!

956
00:35:12,140 --> 00:35:14,140
You recognized my voice right away.

957
00:35:15,620 --> 00:35:16,230
Hang on.

958
00:35:16,230 --> 00:35:17,280
Hang on a second.

959
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:18,460
What are you doing?

960
00:35:18,550 --> 00:35:19,400
I'm in the classroom.

961
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:20,440
Wait a second.

962
00:35:21,140 --> 00:35:22,000
Okay, waiting.

963
00:35:23,270 --> 00:35:24,910
Well? Are you surprised?

964
00:35:24,930 --> 00:35:27,390
What's going on?
Is this your mobile number?

965
00:35:27,510 --> 00:35:29,190
I just bought it.

966
00:35:29,190 --> 00:35:30,760
I just got the SIM card set up

967
00:35:30,910 --> 00:35:32,340
and put it in,
and I called you right away.

968
00:35:32,340 --> 00:35:34,110
I don't even know what my number is.

969
00:35:34,110 --> 00:35:35,640
Hurry up and save my number.

970
00:35:35,790 --> 00:35:36,960
Save it and send it to me.

971
00:35:36,960 --> 00:35:38,220
Of course I'll save it.

972
00:35:38,360 --> 00:35:40,190
What made you decide to
buy a mobile phone?

973
00:35:40,190 --> 00:35:42,110
So I can get in touch with you more often.

974
00:35:42,110 --> 00:35:44,970
Isn't it great to be able to call
anytime, anywhere?

975
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:46,560
I've been thinking about getting a phone

976
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:48,160
every single day, non-stop,

977
00:35:48,490 --> 00:35:49,820
and I finally bought it.

978
00:35:51,320 --> 00:35:52,780
But mobile phones are so expensive.

979
00:35:52,780 --> 00:35:54,550
Do you have any money left
after buying it?

980
00:35:54,550 --> 00:35:56,610
It's not expensive—just pocket change.

981
00:35:56,610 --> 00:35:58,070
Let me tell you, right now,

982
00:35:58,110 --> 00:35:59,550
at our dance hall

983
00:35:59,880 --> 00:36:01,280
and our clothing stall,

984
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:02,480
business is booming.

985
00:36:02,550 --> 00:36:03,590
We can't even keep up with the demand.

986
00:36:03,590 --> 00:36:04,840
Every day, a big crowd

987
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:07,360
surrounds my caravan to buy stuff.

988
00:36:07,920 --> 00:36:10,280
The dance hall is flourishing too—

989
00:36:10,510 --> 00:36:11,400
busier and more vibrant than ever,

990
00:36:11,400 --> 00:36:12,590
with more and more customers coming in.

991
00:36:12,590 --> 00:36:14,190
We're basically considered

992
00:36:14,760 --> 00:36:16,620
a local landmark around here now.

993
00:36:17,230 --> 00:36:19,800
Every evening, after work,
everyone comes here.

994
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:21,320
Anyway, I've got a phone now.

995
00:36:21,320 --> 00:36:22,960
Contact me anytime.

996
00:36:23,110 --> 00:36:24,280
Give me a call whenever you're free.

997
00:36:24,280 --> 00:36:26,310
I feel uneasy if this phone just
sits in my pocket without ringing.

998
00:36:26,310 --> 00:36:26,840
Alright.

999
00:36:27,070 --> 00:36:28,170
You're in class, aren't you?

1000
00:36:28,170 --> 00:36:29,700
Go back to class. It's okay.

1001
00:36:32,470 --> 00:36:33,840
I'm so busy.

1002
00:36:36,220 --> 00:36:38,000
Is that all you're having for lunch?

1003
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:39,460
There's your coffee, too.

1004
00:36:39,680 --> 00:36:41,480
I have a meeting this afternoon.

1005
00:36:41,510 --> 00:36:43,310
What did you want to see me about?

1006
00:36:47,110 --> 00:36:50,230
You know
I applied to study in France, right?

1007
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:54,370
And I passed the French exam
a couple of days ago.

1008
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:58,150
But I still haven't decided
whether to go or not.

1009
00:36:58,150 --> 00:37:00,150
I thought you already decided to go.

1010
00:37:00,670 --> 00:37:02,000
No, I haven't.

1011
00:37:02,150 --> 00:37:05,920
Every time I think about going to France,

1012
00:37:06,510 --> 00:37:08,840
all I can think of is that
I'd have to be apart from Xiaoman.

1013
00:37:08,840 --> 00:37:11,170
What if we don't see each other
for 2 years?

1014
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:13,070
When I came to Shanghai,

1015
00:37:13,070 --> 00:37:14,270
wasn't my hope just to

1016
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:17,230
be with Xiaoman forever?

1017
00:37:17,230 --> 00:37:19,280
How could we end up
drifting further apart?

1018
00:37:19,280 --> 00:37:22,080
Because you're going to a place
even further away.

1019
00:37:22,480 --> 00:37:23,630
No, I haven't.

1020
00:37:23,630 --> 00:37:25,380
I'm just saying that
I was worried if I hesitated,

1021
00:37:25,380 --> 00:37:26,770
I'd miss the opportunity.

1022
00:37:26,770 --> 00:37:30,410
Even if the admission letter comes later,

1023
00:37:30,440 --> 00:37:32,170
I can still turn it down, right?

1024
00:37:33,630 --> 00:37:35,630
What does Xiaoman think about this?

1025
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:38,930
He doesn't know yet.

1026
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:41,420
You haven't told Xiaoman?

1027
00:37:44,550 --> 00:37:47,960
I wanted to wait until
the National Day holiday,

1028
00:37:47,960 --> 00:37:49,470
when I go back to East Chemical Plant,
to tell him.

1029
00:37:49,470 --> 00:37:50,930
So, what answer do you hope

1030
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:53,670
to hear from Xiaoman?

1031
00:37:54,640 --> 00:37:56,640
That there's a bright future ahead,

1032
00:37:57,040 --> 00:37:59,240
and someone behind you still loves you?

1033
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:00,880
Not that.

1034
00:38:02,710 --> 00:38:05,100
Then do you hope Xiaoman lets you go,

1035
00:38:05,430 --> 00:38:07,390
so you can leave without guilt?

1036
00:38:07,410 --> 00:38:09,140
Of course not. Even more wrong.

1037
00:38:14,030 --> 00:38:17,090
It's just... We've known each other
since we were kids,

1038
00:38:18,510 --> 00:38:19,710
for over 10 years.

1039
00:38:20,840 --> 00:38:22,240
We finally got together,

1040
00:38:23,150 --> 00:38:24,610
and it's been over 3 years.

1041
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:27,480
But the time we actually spent together

1042
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:30,110
wasn't that much.

1043
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:33,400
I can't bear to leave him.

1044
00:38:35,070 --> 00:38:36,470
I still want to be with him

1045
00:38:37,630 --> 00:38:39,440
properly in the future.

1046
00:38:39,630 --> 00:38:41,150
If studying in France

1047
00:38:41,710 --> 00:38:43,510
was a sudden notice

1048
00:38:43,840 --> 00:38:45,500
and you had to leave tomorrow;

1049
00:38:45,710 --> 00:38:46,920
or let's say,

1050
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:49,730
you had to decide within a week,

1051
00:38:50,590 --> 00:38:54,050
then I could totally understand
how you're feeling right now.

1052
00:38:54,370 --> 00:38:56,280
But you spent the whole summer

1053
00:38:56,480 --> 00:38:57,880
passing the French exam,

1054
00:38:58,990 --> 00:39:01,720
yet you couldn't spare 5 minutes
to call Xiaoman?

1055
00:39:05,400 --> 00:39:06,760
But how can feelings

1056
00:39:06,760 --> 00:39:08,400
be explained clearly?

1057
00:39:09,630 --> 00:39:11,430
Feelings are just complicated.

1058
00:39:11,760 --> 00:39:12,760
During this time,

1059
00:39:13,430 --> 00:39:14,830
I've been suffering too.

1060
00:39:20,860 --> 00:39:22,970
Actually, you don't need my advice.

1061
00:39:24,110 --> 00:39:26,640
You just need me to tell you
that you're right.

1062
00:39:28,630 --> 00:39:30,090
I can't help you with that.

1063
00:39:37,630 --> 00:39:38,360
Xiaodan.

1064
00:39:38,880 --> 00:39:40,800
If I have any advice for you,

1065
00:39:42,190 --> 00:39:44,450
it's to tell Xiaoman as soon as possible.

1066
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:48,000
He needs even more time to think it over.

1067
00:39:50,630 --> 00:39:51,240
I'm off.

1068
00:40:08,730 --> 00:40:11,500
Son, after you get back to Shanghai,

1069
00:40:11,590 --> 00:40:13,590
you need to swallow your pride a bit.

1070
00:40:13,670 --> 00:40:14,590
With your leaders,

1071
00:40:14,590 --> 00:40:15,840
you need to socialize with them

1072
00:40:15,840 --> 00:40:17,360
and give gifts when you should.

1073
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:18,110
I've got everything ready for you.

1074
00:40:18,110 --> 00:40:19,480
Take it with you later, got that?

1075
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:20,960
Why royal jelly again?

1076
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:22,100
Haven't we learned our lesson?

1077
00:40:22,100 --> 00:40:23,500
What royal jelly?

1078
00:40:23,520 --> 00:40:25,380
Your dad asked a good friend of his

1079
00:40:25,630 --> 00:40:27,030
to buy this from the Changbai Mountains.

1080
00:40:27,030 --> 00:40:29,960
This is pure ginseng extract.
It's super expensive.

1081
00:40:30,460 --> 00:40:31,860
Wasting money like that.

1082
00:40:32,580 --> 00:40:33,250
Alright, alright.

1083
00:40:33,250 --> 00:40:34,150
You young people.

1084
00:40:34,150 --> 00:40:35,760
I knew you'd look down on this.

1085
00:40:35,760 --> 00:40:36,860
But let me tell you something—

1086
00:40:36,860 --> 00:40:38,360
the ways of the world

1087
00:40:38,360 --> 00:40:39,510
never change.

1088
00:40:40,510 --> 00:40:42,000
Take your previous internship—

1089
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:43,920
since you didn't get along well
with the leadership,

1090
00:40:43,920 --> 00:40:45,880
how could they possibly keep you on?

1091
00:40:45,880 --> 00:40:46,800
We're back.

1092
00:40:47,070 --> 00:40:48,280
-You're back.
-Close the door.

1093
00:40:48,280 --> 00:40:49,660
Wash your hands. We'll eat in a bit.

1094
00:40:49,660 --> 00:40:50,860
-Okay.
-You're back.

1095
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:54,840
-Son.
-What do you want to drink?

1096
00:40:54,840 --> 00:40:55,230
Soda?

1097
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:56,800
-Yeah, Cola.
-Our family

1098
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:59,550
still hasn't paid off all the debt

1099
00:40:59,570 --> 00:41:01,970
from that whole fake royal jelly incident.

1100
00:41:02,510 --> 00:41:03,800
But don't you worry about that.

1101
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:04,960
Your mom and I
can work another couple of years,

1102
00:41:04,960 --> 00:41:06,290
and we'll pay it all off.

1103
00:41:06,880 --> 00:41:08,320
What I'm trying to say is,

1104
00:41:09,760 --> 00:41:11,000
your mom is reluctant to

1105
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:13,260
spend on herself now, on food or clothes.

1106
00:41:14,280 --> 00:41:15,000
So

1107
00:41:15,030 --> 00:41:16,400
if you can successfully

1108
00:41:16,400 --> 00:41:17,860
get into a good workplace,

1109
00:41:18,670 --> 00:41:19,590
your mom will be able to

1110
00:41:19,590 --> 00:41:21,510
enjoy a more comfortable life sooner,

1111
00:41:21,510 --> 00:41:22,230
right?

1112
00:41:22,360 --> 00:41:23,620
Yeah, pour him a drink.

1113
00:41:27,510 --> 00:41:29,390
If you can swallow your pride a bit

1114
00:41:29,410 --> 00:41:31,210
and give some gifts to your boss,

1115
00:41:32,450 --> 00:41:35,310
just think of it as showing filial piety
to your mom.

1116
00:41:37,030 --> 00:41:39,320
Coming up, the last dish—the grand finale.

1117
00:41:39,320 --> 00:41:40,070
Come on. Here.

1118
00:41:40,070 --> 00:41:40,920
There're way too many dishes.

1119
00:41:40,920 --> 00:41:41,960
This is not the grand finale.

1120
00:41:41,960 --> 00:41:43,280
It's the one following this.

1121
00:41:43,280 --> 00:41:44,150
That's the grand finale.

1122
00:41:44,150 --> 00:41:45,550
So it's a cold salad, huh?

1123
00:41:45,760 --> 00:41:47,230
It's a feast, Uncle.

1124
00:41:47,320 --> 00:41:49,000
Here, put the meat dish next to Xiaodan.

1125
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:49,760
Come on, eat up.

1126
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:51,110
Xiaodan, don't stand on ceremony.

1127
00:41:51,110 --> 00:41:52,000
Make yourself at home.

1128
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:52,760
Thank you, Auntie.

1129
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:53,590
Have some more meat.

1130
00:41:53,590 --> 00:41:54,840
Time truly flies.

1131
00:41:55,580 --> 00:41:57,910
Xiaodan is already a senior in college.

1132
00:41:58,240 --> 00:41:59,190
Still getting taller in your senior year.

1133
00:41:59,190 --> 00:42:01,590
Where are you planning to
do your internship?

1134
00:42:01,590 --> 00:42:02,070
Well...

1135
00:42:03,110 --> 00:42:04,760
I don't know. I haven't decided yet.

1136
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:06,760
Why should you worry about Xiaodan?

1137
00:42:06,960 --> 00:42:08,480
With a word from Chief Engineer Yan,

1138
00:42:08,480 --> 00:42:10,070
she can get into any top workplace.

1139
00:42:10,070 --> 00:42:10,590
That's true.

1140
00:42:10,590 --> 00:42:11,150
You bet.

1141
00:42:11,800 --> 00:42:12,230
Then

1142
00:42:13,920 --> 00:42:15,800
I'd like to ask you for a favor.

1143
00:42:16,480 --> 00:42:17,360
You see, if Chief Engineer Yan

1144
00:42:17,360 --> 00:42:18,540
comes across any other good job openings,

1145
00:42:18,540 --> 00:42:19,400
please keep us in mind.

1146
00:42:19,400 --> 00:42:20,530
Keep Xia Lei in mind.

1147
00:42:20,670 --> 00:42:21,440
-No problem.
-That's right.

1148
00:42:21,440 --> 00:42:21,920
Here.

1149
00:42:22,150 --> 00:42:23,000
I... I'm good.

1150
00:42:23,710 --> 00:42:24,760
What do you mean you're good? This kid...

1151
00:42:24,760 --> 00:42:26,020
H-He's just stubborn.

1152
00:42:26,110 --> 00:42:26,630
Just distribute that rice.

1153
00:42:26,630 --> 00:42:28,110
It's not like Chief Engineer Yan
is a stranger or something.

1154
00:42:28,110 --> 00:42:29,630
You keep saying
you want to rely on yourself,

1155
00:42:29,630 --> 00:42:31,760
but that internet thing you did before

1156
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:33,710
didn't amount to anything, did it?

1157
00:42:33,710 --> 00:42:34,710
Is this much rice enough for you?

1158
00:42:34,710 --> 00:42:35,110
Yes.

1159
00:42:35,230 --> 00:42:35,630
Auntie,

1160
00:42:35,630 --> 00:42:37,710
Xia Lei did that internet business
pretty well.

1161
00:42:37,710 --> 00:42:39,670
It only failed because

1162
00:42:39,670 --> 00:42:40,820
he tried to find work for me.

1163
00:42:40,820 --> 00:42:42,320
No, it had nothing to do with you.

1164
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:43,630
Don't overthink it, Xiaoman.

1165
00:42:43,630 --> 00:42:44,630
That's not what I meant.

1166
00:42:44,630 --> 00:42:46,190
I just think that this internet business

1167
00:42:46,190 --> 00:42:47,600
isn't a proper job.

1168
00:42:47,760 --> 00:42:49,920
Since he finally made it
all the way to Shanghai,

1169
00:42:49,920 --> 00:42:52,060
he should find a big company.

1170
00:42:52,230 --> 00:42:53,160
Don't you agree?

1171
00:42:54,110 --> 00:42:55,920
Well, Auntie, with Xia Lei's abilities,

1172
00:42:55,920 --> 00:42:56,760
he'll be fine.

1173
00:42:56,760 --> 00:42:58,710
Companies will be fighting over him.

1174
00:42:58,710 --> 00:43:00,070
But I'll also talk to my dad.

1175
00:43:00,070 --> 00:43:02,000
I'll ask him to help keep an eye out.

1176
00:43:02,400 --> 00:43:03,200
Right, right.

1177
00:43:03,440 --> 00:43:04,540
Come on, have some more meat.
